As of the 2010 [[census]],<ref name=USCB>{{cite web|last=U.S. Census Bureau|title=2010 Population Finder|url=https://www.census.gov/popfinder/?fl=35:3512500|access-date=September 3, 2012}}</ref> there were 996 people living in the town. The racial makeup of the town was 78.71% White, 0.70% African American, 2.61% American Indian, 14.16% Other, and 3.82% identified as two or more. Hispanics of any race were 43.57% of the population. Of the population, 54.72% were men and 45.28% were women. Of these, 15.96% were under the age of 18, 24.50% were over 65, and 59.54% were between 18 and 65.

